<section aria-labelledby="bookmarklet-heading">
  <h2 id="bookmarklet-heading" class="section-title">Browser Bookmarklet</h2>

  <div class="card mb-md">
    <h3 class="card__title mb-md">Scan with Pally</h3>
    <p class="form-hint mb-md">
      Drag the button below to your browser's bookmark bar. Then visit any website and click it to
      open a new Pally scan with the URL pre-filled.
    </p>

    <div style="text-align:center; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
      <a class="btn btn--primary"
         href="javascript:void(function(){var d='{{dashboardUrl}}';var u=encodeURIComponent(window.location.href);window.open(d+'/scan/new?prefill='+u,'_blank');})()"
         onclick="event.preventDefault(); alert('Drag this button to your bookmark bar instead of clicking it.');"
         draggable="true"
         aria-label="Drag this link to your bookmark bar to install the Pally bookmarklet">
        Scan with Pally
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card mb-md">
    <h3 class="card__title mb-md">How to Use</h3>
    <ol style="padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.8;">
      <li><strong>Drag</strong> the "Scan with Pally" button above to your browser's bookmark bar.</li>
      <li><strong>Visit</strong> any website you want to scan for accessibility issues.</li>
      <li><strong>Click</strong> the bookmark &mdash; Pally opens in a new tab with the URL pre-filled and ready to scan.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="card mb-md">
    <h3 class="card__title mb-md">Manual Installation</h3>
    <p class="form-hint mb-sm">
      If drag-and-drop does not work, create a new bookmark manually and paste the following code as the URL:
    </p>
    <pre style="background: var(--bg-muted, #f4f5f7); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 6px; overflow-x: auto; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.5;"><code>javascript:void(function(){var d='{{dashboardUrl}}';var u=encodeURIComponent(window.location.href);window.open(d+'/scan/new?prefill='+u,'_blank');})()</code></pre>
  </div>

  <div class="card mb-md">
    <h3 class="card__title mb-md">Requirements</h3>
    <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.8;">
      <li>The Pally dashboard must be running and accessible at <code>{{dashboardUrl}}</code>.</li>
      <li>You must be logged in to the dashboard for the scan to start.</li>
      <li>Pop-up blockers may need to allow pop-ups from the site you are scanning.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
